Would you like to read tips on horse training and horse racing?
When you welcome a new horse, the training period begins.
During the training period, you can perform "feeding" and "training" every day.
Feeding the horse increases its "affection level."
The higher the affection level, the greater the training effect.
There are three types of training: "Speed," "Power," and "Stamina,"
which can increase each respective stat.
Training when the horse's stamina is low may result in failure.
Be careful, as failure will decrease the affection level.
Take good care of the horse every day to raise a strong horse.
Once the training period is over, the horse can participate in horse races.
Horse races are held twice a month, on the 7th and 14th.
Races have grades, with G3 → G2 → G1 increasing in difficulty,
and the prize money for winning also increases.
Once the horse is entered into the race, all you can do is watch and cheer.
The outcome is determined by the horse's stats, skills, and a bit of luck.
Winning first place earns you the trophy for each race.
Try raising a strong horse and challenging the horse races.
